1
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:13,467
<i> I will never lose you again.</i>

2
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:17,533
<i>Are you going to fool Emma again
after leaving her for Jade?</i>

3
00:00:17,667 --> 00:00:18,700
<i> No!</i>

4
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:19,967
<i> Jade's here, Dan.</i>

5
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:21,233
<i> Go hide!</i>

6
00:00:21,367 --> 00:00:21,967
<i> Mom?</i>

7
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:24,300
<i> That means I got mad at her</i>

8
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:26,567
<i>without even trying
to find out the truth.</i>

9
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:29,467
<i>I really hope
grandmother comes back.</i>

10
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,233
<i> Ligaya? Ligaya, is that you?</i>

11
00:00:31,367 --> 00:00:32,467
<i> Hey! Who are you?</i>

12
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,533
<i> Ligaya!</i>

13
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:34,600
<i> Stop!</i>

14
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:35,467
<i> Let go of me!</i>

15
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:36,767
<i>There seems to be noise outside.</i>

16
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:37,833
<i> Calm down.</i>

17
00:00:37,967 --> 00:00:39,200
<i> It's just the neighbor.</i>

18
00:00:39,333 --> 00:00:40,467
<i> Why are you here?</i>

19
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:41,600
<i> Because I want to think!</i>

20
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:42,767
<i> And why did you follow me?</i>

21
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,967
<i>Can you please
give me some peace, Jade?</i>

22
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:47,200
<i>What I did with Emma
is in the past now.</i>

23
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:49,933
<i>But I will do everything
for her to forgive me</i>

24
00:00:50,067 --> 00:00:51,233
<i> and come back to me again.</i>

25
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,367
<i> Stop it, Logan.</i>

26
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:53,733
<i> No matter what you do,</i>

27
00:00:53,867 --> 00:00:57,133
<i>you can't stop me from getting
back together with my wife.</i>

28
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:40,100
Enjoy your pathetic
little victory.

29
00:01:40,233 --> 00:01:41,333
Because it will be your last.

30
00:01:42,433 --> 00:01:44,400
I will destroy you.

31
00:01:47,633 --> 00:01:48,533
Friend?

32
00:01:49,867 --> 00:01:50,767
Hello.

33
00:01:53,733 --> 00:01:55,300
You're here!

34
00:01:55,433 --> 00:01:58,400
Yes, we've been here
for a while now.

35
00:01:58,533 --> 00:02:00,700
I think you forgot
about your late lunch treat.

36
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:02,600
It's a good thing
that Mookie gave us some snacks.

37
00:02:02,733 --> 00:02:04,567
Oh, yeah!

38
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:07,233
Aunt Jade, are you okay?

39
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:09,900
Why are your clothes dirty?

40
00:02:10,033 --> 00:02:12,167
Don't worry about this,
baby girl.

41
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:16,033
I encountered a weirdo and a
lunatic, and road rage ensued.

42
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:19,900
She went wild until everything
was already chaotic.

43
00:02:20,033 --> 00:02:23,000
And this happened.
But don't worry, I'm fine.

44
00:02:23,133 --> 00:02:25,133
Anyway, let's eat.

45
00:02:25,267 --> 00:02:27,433
Danilo's on his way home, too.

46
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:28,900
Wait. Here's the thing.

47
00:02:29,033 --> 00:02:33,400
Friend, we were talking
about Ligaya.

48
00:02:33,533 --> 00:02:39,367
As you know, we haven't heard
anything yet about our BFF.

49
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:40,533
Correct.

50
00:02:40,667 --> 00:02:44,633
You saw her last
before she went to Cebu, right?

51
00:02:44,767 --> 00:02:46,733
It's been so long.

52
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,367
Maybe there's something
you know that we don't.

53
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,033
Well, you know what?

54
00:02:51,167 --> 00:02:53,433
I'm just as clueless as you are.

55
00:02:53,567 --> 00:02:55,333
Is that your final answer, Jade?

56
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:57,467
Yeah.

57
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,167
Why?

58
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:01,500
Are you doubting me?

59
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:03,967
Come on, friend!
Let's not ruin the vibe.

60
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:05,033
Come on, let's eat.

61
00:03:05,167 --> 00:03:08,167
- I'll prepare the...
- Wow, hold on!

62
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:11,167
You don't seem to care
about your mom.

63
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,467
Excuse me?

64
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:19,767
Are you saying that
I don't worry for my mom?

65
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:22,600
I also don't know
where she is, like you.

66
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:24,600
Is that my fault?

67
00:03:24,733 --> 00:03:28,533
And now you're accusing me
of not thinking about her?

68
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:30,533
That I'm not worried about her?

69
00:03:30,667 --> 00:03:33,500
That I don't care about
my mother? Is that it?

70
00:03:33,633 --> 00:03:36,000
- Aunt Jade...
- Is that what you think of me?

71
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:37,667
- I'm also looking for my mom.
- Aunt Jade...

72
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,767
But I also don't know
where she is.

73
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:40,833
You're so mean!

74
00:03:40,967 --> 00:03:42,533
Aunt Jade, that's enough.

75
00:03:42,667 --> 00:03:44,733
I'll prepare our food.

76
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:58,267
Of course, she doesn't.

77
00:04:37,733 --> 00:04:39,367
Hey!

78
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:40,900
What's that? Why are you
staring into nothing?

79
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,200
Could you wait until later

80
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:45,200
to fantasize about the kiss
that happened?

81
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:46,633
Is that okay?

82
00:04:46,767 --> 00:04:49,600
Why did you hide from Jade?

83
00:04:49,733 --> 00:04:51,633
Because I know
where it would lead.

84
00:04:51,767 --> 00:04:53,400
In a fight.

85
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:56,267
And I want her to look like
a fool like what she did to me.

86
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,567
My God!

87
00:04:57,700 --> 00:05:01,600
You're strong enough to fight
that queen of vampiric creature.

88
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:03,533
I know that, Flor.

89
00:05:03,667 --> 00:05:06,200
But I don't want to think
about her for now.

90
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:09,100
Talking to Danilo matters more.

91
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:13,967
What about Logan?

92
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:16,067
Have you already reconciled?

93
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:18,700
Let's give him time to cool off.

94
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:22,200
And I don't want to think
about other people for now.

95
00:05:22,333 --> 00:05:25,333
Danilo and Mookie
matter to me the most.

96
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:28,267
I need to tell them
what Jade really did to me.

97
00:05:29,567 --> 00:05:31,367
So that I can take them back.

98
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:33,267
What about Danilo?

99
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,267
When will you and Danilo
see each other again?

100
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,400
Boss,

101
00:05:44,533 --> 00:05:46,733
it looks like Danilo
won't back down from you.

102
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:50,300
And you think I'll back down?

103
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:53,733
You're at a disadvantage
against him.

104
00:05:53,867 --> 00:05:55,467
Because Emma loves him.

105
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:58,733
That won't be a problem.

106
00:05:58,867 --> 00:06:00,433
I have a solution to that.

107
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,800
How?

108
00:06:06,267 --> 00:06:08,567
The anger Emma felt

109
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:12,833
when she found out
she was replaced by Jade...

110
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:17,033
I will use that to my advantage.

111
00:06:17,167 --> 00:06:20,333
I will remind her every day...

112
00:06:20,467 --> 00:06:24,133
how her fake husband
betrayed her.

113
00:06:29,033 --> 00:06:31,167
Sounds like a good plan.

114
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:33,200
But something seems missing.

115
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:37,467
What are you doing here?

116
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,867
I came to see you.

117
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,367
Obviously.

118
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:45,700
Marco, leave us for now.

119
00:06:51,633 --> 00:06:54,167
I think I know why you're here.

120
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:59,567
You want to collaborate with me
against Emma and Danilo.

121
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:00,700
Is that correct?

122
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:06,533
So...

123
00:07:06,667 --> 00:07:09,367
- I'm thinking...
- Wait, wait, wait!

124
00:07:11,767 --> 00:07:13,200
You're so assuming.

125
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:14,767
Did I say yes?

126
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,167
I thought...

127
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,400
you were okay with...

128
00:07:21,533 --> 00:07:23,300
us planning together?

129
00:07:25,767 --> 00:07:27,467
Let me remind you.

130
00:07:28,533 --> 00:07:31,967
After what you did to me
in Japan...

131
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,800
I no longer trust you.

132
00:07:34,933 --> 00:07:36,133
Never again.

133
00:07:38,967 --> 00:07:41,133
That was so long ago.

134
00:07:41,267 --> 00:07:43,033
Get over it.

135
00:07:43,167 --> 00:07:44,800
Forget whatever happened
between you...

136
00:07:44,933 --> 00:07:48,267
between us in Japan...

137
00:07:48,433 --> 00:07:49,433
forget about it.

138
00:07:50,767 --> 00:07:52,600
Of course,
I've already forgotten.

139
00:07:53,667 --> 00:07:57,067
But I've also forgotten
my trust in you.

140
00:07:58,933 --> 00:08:04,267
So whatever you want to do
against Emma and Danilo,

141
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,667
do it yourself.

142
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:10,867
Just make sure
you won't hurt Emma.

143
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,333
Because you won't like
what I'll do to you

144
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:16,300
once you touch her.

145
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:21,367
I thought you were a tough guy.

146
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:26,100
Turns out, you're also foolish
when it comes to women.

147
00:08:29,167 --> 00:08:30,800
Well, Jade...

148
00:08:30,933 --> 00:08:33,767
you know me
when it comes to love.

149
00:08:35,167 --> 00:08:36,900
You experienced it yourself,
remember?

150
00:08:37,967 --> 00:08:39,833
For someone like you

151
00:08:39,967 --> 00:08:42,000
who wasn't deserving of love...

152
00:08:42,133 --> 00:08:44,333
I became a fool.

153
00:08:44,467 --> 00:08:46,200
What more with Emma?

154
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,333
She's far better than you.

155
00:08:48,467 --> 00:08:49,467
Emma.

156
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:51,533
Jade.

157
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:54,267
So, whatever.

158
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:59,067
Do whatever you like
to keep Danilo away from Emma.

159
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:02,500
But never hurt her.

160
00:09:03,867 --> 00:09:05,300
I might kill you.

161
00:09:07,467 --> 00:09:08,767
Is that a threat?

162
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:11,467
So pathetic.

163
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,933
But fine,

164
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:19,233
it's up to you if you don't
want to accept my help.

165
00:09:19,367 --> 00:09:24,767
Your plan to remind Emma
how Danilo hurt her?

166
00:09:28,033 --> 00:09:30,000
So lame.

167
00:09:30,133 --> 00:09:32,500
I'm sure you'll fail.

168
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,533
Who says...

169
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:46,367
that's my only plan?

170
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:52,800
So there's more?

171
00:09:52,933 --> 00:09:54,100
<i> We'll go to Singapore.</i>

172
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:55,700
<i> I have businesses there.</i>

173
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:59,033
<i>I'll make you a manager
in one of my businesses.</i>

174
00:09:59,167 --> 00:10:00,933
So, what's the other plan?

175
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:15,067
Damn you, Logan.

176
00:10:40,367 --> 00:10:42,400
What are you planning this time,
Emma?

177
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:41,300
Miss.

178
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:42,600
Miss, I'll check in.

179
00:11:42,733 --> 00:11:44,800
Short time. Three hours.

180
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:45,833
Okay.

181
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:50,567
Here you go, Sir.

182
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:52,400
- Second floor, 2C.
- Second floor, 2C.

183
00:11:52,533 --> 00:11:53,733
Okay, copy.

184
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,567
- Thank you.
- Anytime.

185
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:20,100
Danilo?

186
00:12:21,767 --> 00:12:22,733
Motel?

187
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,000
Don't tell me...

188
00:12:37,033 --> 00:12:37,567
Yes, Ma'am?

189
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:39,867
Miss, guest for room 2C.

190
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,100
Okay, please wait.

191
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,433
Hello, Sir?

192
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:45,400
Expected guest?

193
00:12:45,533 --> 00:12:46,267
Okay.

194
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,133
Yes, Ma'am.
You can go upstairs now.

195
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:34,600
Ma'am?

196
00:13:35,767 --> 00:13:36,533
Ma'am.

197
00:13:39,267 --> 00:13:40,300
Ma'am, Ma'am, Ma'am.

198
00:13:40,433 --> 00:13:41,833
Ma'am.

199
00:13:41,967 --> 00:13:43,200
Where are you going, Ma'am?

200
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:46,967
I saw my husband
go inside with his mistress!

201
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:48,433
Are you sure, Ma'am?

202
00:13:48,567 --> 00:13:50,367
I'm sure. I saw it with my own
two eyes.

203
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:54,133
So let me in. Because if not,
I will make a scene.

204
00:13:58,267 --> 00:13:59,867
Calm down.

205
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,733
Don't be overacting.

206
00:14:01,867 --> 00:14:04,000
Don't be so dramatic.

207
00:14:04,133 --> 00:14:05,433
I also have a husband...

208
00:14:06,567 --> 00:14:08,100
who has a mistress.

209
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:10,733
If that's the case...

210
00:14:10,867 --> 00:14:13,867
you understand how I feel.

211
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,467
Of course.

212
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:17,133
So, go.

213
00:14:17,267 --> 00:14:20,033
Fight for the legal wives.

214
00:14:20,167 --> 00:14:23,000
Mistresses should be whipped.

215
00:14:23,133 --> 00:14:24,900
Nailed to the cross.

216
00:14:25,033 --> 00:14:26,267
Buried alive.

217
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,067
Burned in hell.

218
00:14:28,233 --> 00:14:33,200
So, go ahead, Ma'am.
They're on the second floor, 2C.

219
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:34,600
Go, go, go, Ma'am.

220
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:39,833
Are you sure
Jade didn't follow you?

221
00:14:39,967 --> 00:14:41,200
Yes, Emma. She's leaving.

222
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:45,000
She'll meet
with Leticia and Astrid.

223
00:14:45,133 --> 00:14:47,733
Why did you decide to meet here?

224
00:14:47,867 --> 00:14:51,267
Because this is a safe place
to talk.

225
00:14:59,467 --> 00:15:00,633
I thought...

226
00:15:01,733 --> 00:15:02,600
Oh, please.

227
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:03,967
Let's fix this first.

228
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:07,433
I brought the proof that Jade
drove me insane in Havenwood.

229
00:15:07,567 --> 00:15:09,000
Here, read it.

230
00:15:26,167 --> 00:15:27,133
Emma, there seems to be a fire.

231
00:15:27,267 --> 00:15:28,300
- What?
- Come on, let's go.

232
00:15:28,433 --> 00:15:29,467
Let's hurry!

233
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:38,900
Jade?

234
00:15:39,033 --> 00:15:41,033
I knew it.

235
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:43,033
What?

236
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:45,733
Aren't you going to leave
Danilo alone?

237
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:47,367
I won't leave my husband alone

238
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:50,000
until he knows
everything that you did to me!

239
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:51,300
And I will never
let you win again.

240
00:15:51,433 --> 00:15:54,267
So, leave!
Because you're not invited here!

241
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:57,467
I won't leave without Danilo!

242
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,300
- Jade!
- Let's go!

243
00:15:58,433 --> 00:16:00,333
Jade, can you please leave?

244
00:16:00,467 --> 00:16:02,400
Let my wife and I talk.

245
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,733
Isn't it clear to you yet?

246
00:16:04,867 --> 00:16:06,533
We're done.

247
00:16:06,667 --> 00:16:09,367
That's why I called off
the wedding.

248
00:16:09,533 --> 00:16:11,000
Jade, it's Emma I love.

249
00:16:11,133 --> 00:16:11,933
No.

250
00:16:12,067 --> 00:16:13,100
No one else.

251
00:16:13,233 --> 00:16:16,100
No, Danilo.
I won't let that happen.

252
00:16:16,233 --> 00:16:21,000
If I have to get rid
of this woman, I will do so!

253
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:22,800
- Jade!
- You're really something else!

254
00:16:22,933 --> 00:16:24,333
Jade!

255
00:16:24,467 --> 00:16:25,533
Stop it! That's enough!

256
00:16:25,667 --> 00:16:27,267
You're also taking Danilo away
from me!

257
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,333
Jade!

258
00:16:28,467 --> 00:16:30,267
- Let go of me!
- Emma! Jade! stop it!

259
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:32,633
You're more shameless!

260
00:16:32,767 --> 00:16:34,267
Stop it!

261
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,933
That's enough! Stop it!

262
00:16:38,733 --> 00:16:40,500
Jade, stop it!

263
00:16:40,633 --> 00:16:41,733
Jade!

264
00:16:41,900 --> 00:16:43,233
Jade, stop!

265
00:16:43,367 --> 00:16:44,767
Ouch!

266
00:16:44,900 --> 00:16:47,567
What are you doing? Emma, stop!
Stop it!

267
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:49,500
Emma, that's enough! Emma, stop!

268
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:52,067
Emma, that's enough!

269
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:52,967
Stop!

270
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:54,633
Emma!

271
00:16:54,767 --> 00:16:57,000
Emma! Emma, that's enough!

272
00:16:57,133 --> 00:16:58,900
You're the one messing
everything up!

273
00:16:59,033 --> 00:17:00,933
- Let me go, you animal!
- That's enough!

274
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:02,133
Stop!

275
00:17:02,267 --> 00:17:03,233
Jade! Emma!

276
00:17:03,367 --> 00:17:06,333
- Emma, stop it!
- You should stop, you woman!

277
00:17:06,467 --> 00:17:07,167
Emma.

278
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:08,967
That's enough! Stop!

279
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:11,367
What's wrong with you two?
Stop this.

280
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:12,367
Jade! Jade!

281
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:13,700
- Let go of me!
- Stop it.

282
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:15,733
You really are an animal!

283
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:21,600
- Danilo!
- Dan!

284
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:23,467
- Dan!
- Danilo!

285
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:24,733
No!

286
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:26,333
- Danilo!
- Danilo!

287
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:28,233
- Danilo!
- Danilo!

288
00:17:28,467 --> 00:17:30,067
Look what you did!

289
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:32,167
This is all your fault.

290
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:34,567
Instead of blaming me,
call an ambulance!

291
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:35,933
Why me?

292
00:17:36,067 --> 00:17:37,600
Aren't you the wife?

293
00:17:37,733 --> 00:17:38,800
Do it yourself!

294
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:40,467
If something bad happens
to Danilo,

295
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:43,200
there's no one to blame but you!

296
00:17:44,467 --> 00:17:46,167
- Dan!
- Dan!

297
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,033
- Don't touch his head.
- Dan!

298
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,600
- Dan!
- Dan!

299
00:17:49,733 --> 00:17:51,067
- Dan, wake up!
- Dan.

300
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:53,800
- Dan!
- Help!

301
00:17:53,933 --> 00:17:55,700
- Help!
- Please help us!

302
00:17:55,833 --> 00:17:57,333
Help!

303
00:18:02,633 --> 00:18:04,400
Boss, that's enough.

304
00:18:04,533 --> 00:18:06,100
That's not good for your liver.

305
00:18:06,233 --> 00:18:08,000
Pour all of it.

306
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:13,533
I don't care
even if my liver burns.

307
00:18:13,667 --> 00:18:16,367
I wish my heart would burn, too.

308
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:19,067
After all, it's completely
shattered because of Emma.

309
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,833
You know what, Marco?

310
00:18:23,967 --> 00:18:28,233
I did everything for Emma so
that she would recover. And...

311
00:18:29,967 --> 00:18:32,233
she'll still choose Danilo?

312
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,533
He betrayed her,

313
00:18:35,667 --> 00:18:38,033
but he's still the one
she loves.

314
00:18:38,167 --> 00:18:39,700
I don't get it!

315
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:42,633
I don't get it, Marco!

316
00:18:43,133 --> 00:18:45,533
I think that's how life is.

317
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,533
The one who is more serious...

318
00:18:49,667 --> 00:18:51,233
ends up losing.

319
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:55,000
I've already given her
quite a lot.

320
00:18:57,233 --> 00:18:59,300
In terms of investment...

321
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:02,600
I'm just waiting to reap
the returns.

322
00:19:04,467 --> 00:19:06,267
I won't let him win.

323
00:19:07,933 --> 00:19:10,100
I will show Emma...

324
00:19:11,133 --> 00:19:13,167
that I deserve to be with her.

325
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:26,567
Danilo!

326
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:28,800
Dan?

327
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:29,900
Dan?

328
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:31,833
Ma'am, please stay here.

329
00:19:31,967 --> 00:19:32,633
What?

330
00:19:32,767 --> 00:19:34,367
Please stay here.

331
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:39,500
Go home, Emma.
You're not needed here.

332
00:19:40,967 --> 00:19:45,233
I deserve to be here
because I'm the wife!

333
00:19:45,367 --> 00:19:46,767
You better prepare.

334
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:49,767
I'll file an assault
and attempted murder case.

335
00:19:51,767 --> 00:19:53,367
Go ahead.

336
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:54,900
Is that a threat?

337
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,700
Then do it.

338
00:19:57,833 --> 00:19:59,533
I will sue you, too.

339
00:19:59,667 --> 00:20:01,000
With what?

340
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:02,200
Assault?

341
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:04,100
Attempted murder, too?

342
00:20:04,233 --> 00:20:06,900
Let me remind you,
you're the one who attacked us.

343
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:08,300
What case will you file
against me?

344
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,400
What? There's none, right?

345
00:20:11,533 --> 00:20:12,833
Has your brain
already gone haywire?

346
00:20:12,967 --> 00:20:14,533
No more nutrients?

347
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:18,767
Or maybe the effects of ZX
haven't worn off on you yet?

348
00:20:20,933 --> 00:20:23,067
So, you did that?

349
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:24,700
You drove me crazy?

350
00:20:26,633 --> 00:20:28,800
You really are a monster!

351
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:33,833
You started it!

352
00:20:33,967 --> 00:20:34,900
I just got even with you!

353
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:35,933
You're a monster!

354
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:38,833
You're like a dog
eating leftover bones!

355
00:20:38,967 --> 00:20:42,900
- And you're like a gecko!
- Stop, you two!

356
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:44,567
Please have some shame!

357
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:46,833
Some patients are trying
to get some rest.

358
00:20:47,867 --> 00:20:50,167
Get out of here
if you can't be stopped!

359
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:57,100
Left first, then right.

360
00:20:57,233 --> 00:20:59,267
- Then wiggle, wiggle.
- What? How do you do that?

361
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,033
You just do it like this.

362
00:21:01,167 --> 00:21:02,800
- My knee hurts.
- Okay.

363
00:21:02,933 --> 00:21:04,833
Right. Wiggle.

364
00:21:05,533 --> 00:21:06,533
- What?
- Left, wiggle.

365
00:21:06,667 --> 00:21:09,733
-Move it like this, then wiggle.
-You can do it.

366
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:11,967
- Not like how you did it.
- That's what I did.

367
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:14,500
Not like that.

368
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:16,467
You need more practice.

369
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:18,600
- Come on. My moves were right.
- Let's do it again.

370
00:21:18,733 --> 00:21:20,333
Here I go again.

371
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:22,467
Zayn...

372
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:24,367
why don't you go home now?

373
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,467
Your mom might start
looking for you.

374
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,600
She might text or call me.

375
00:21:28,733 --> 00:21:30,567
There you go again, Mookie.

376
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:34,333
But I really hope
she warms up to you.

377
00:21:35,867 --> 00:21:39,167
But right now, I'm happy
we're still friends.

378
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:40,800
Of course.

379
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:42,500
Friends.

380
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:43,567
Friends.

381
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:45,167
Friends.

382
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:46,333
Always.

383
00:21:47,567 --> 00:21:49,233
She's good.

384
00:21:57,033 --> 00:21:58,833
Flor!

385
00:21:58,967 --> 00:22:00,067
Hello, Mookie!

386
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,933
My gosh,
this is me driving me nuts!

387
00:22:02,067 --> 00:22:03,400
Why?

388
00:22:03,533 --> 00:22:05,967
I talked to your mom.

389
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:08,800
She said your dad
had an accident.

390
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:09,833
What?

391
00:22:09,967 --> 00:22:11,567
What happened to dad?

392
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:12,867
I don't know.

393
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:13,867
Calm down.

394
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,700
Calm down, okay?

395
00:22:15,867 --> 00:22:18,900
Emma said your dad
was already in the ER.

396
00:22:19,033 --> 00:22:21,467
Everything would be fine.

397
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:23,167
Relax, okay?

398
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:28,133
I'm impressed
by your staying power, Emma.

399
00:22:28,267 --> 00:22:29,900
You should've left hours ago.

400
00:22:30,033 --> 00:22:32,800
And yet, you're still here.

401
00:22:32,933 --> 00:22:35,800
I'm more impressed
by your audacity.

402
00:22:35,933 --> 00:22:37,900
Well, it's now common
for mistresses to be so bold,

403
00:22:38,033 --> 00:22:39,800
gawking like dogs.

404
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:42,933
Just because
you're in the hospital

405
00:22:43,067 --> 00:22:44,567
doesn't mean you're safe.

406
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:50,600
If you don't shut your mouth,
I'll drag you up to the morgue.

407
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:02,633
Who's the wife
of Mr. Danilo Joseco?

408
00:23:02,767 --> 00:23:03,600
- Me.
- Me.

409
00:23:03,733 --> 00:23:06,100
Who is Mrs. Emma Joseco?

410
00:23:06,233 --> 00:23:07,100
It's me.

411
00:23:07,233 --> 00:23:09,767
-Why?
-The patient is looking for you.

412
00:23:09,900 --> 00:23:11,900
You're the only one
he wants to see.

413
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,167
Let's go, Ma'am.

414
00:23:18,067 --> 00:23:19,733
You heard that, right?

415
00:23:20,933 --> 00:23:22,467
He's looking for me.

416
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:26,333
I'm close to taking back
my husband and daughter...

417
00:23:26,467 --> 00:23:29,200
that you keep stealing from me.

418
00:23:29,333 --> 00:23:31,600
What does it feel like to lose

419
00:23:31,733 --> 00:23:33,200
and to have someone taken
from you?

420
00:23:34,733 --> 00:23:37,200
I'm not stealing them.

421
00:23:37,333 --> 00:23:40,467
I'm just taking my family
back from you.

422
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:43,133
You were the first to steal.

423
00:23:43,267 --> 00:23:45,533
Mookie and I were so happy
in our own little bubble

424
00:23:45,667 --> 00:23:48,967
when you suddenly came
and shattered our peace.

425
00:23:50,033 --> 00:23:51,533
Did I hear that correctly?

426
00:23:53,267 --> 00:23:54,300
Olive?

427
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,200
Martinez!

428
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:05,667
Please help me save my wife.

429
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:07,933
Where is she now?
What happened to her?

430
00:24:08,067 --> 00:24:11,500
She's locked up
in Jade Caparas' mansion.

431
00:24:11,633 --> 00:24:14,067
Why don't we just fight
over Danilo?

432
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:16,067
Let's settle it
in a one-on-one fight.

433
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:17,000
Hand-to-hand.

434
00:24:17,133 --> 00:24:21,933
Whoever wins will get Danilo.

435
00:24:22,067 --> 00:24:23,633
Challenge?

436
00:24:23,767 --> 00:24:26,700
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

437
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:28,333
Mookie, sorry.

438
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:31,767
Kutsy and I planned to keep
what Emma said between us.

439
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:34,167
But we're feeling restless.

440
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:35,233
We're really going crazy

441
00:24:35,367 --> 00:24:36,733
with what's happening
between the siblings.

442
00:24:36,867 --> 00:24:38,967
Why don't we make
the prize bigger?

443
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:41,700
It's not just Danilo
that you can win.

444
00:24:41,833 --> 00:24:43,300
You can also win Mookie.

445
00:24:43,433 --> 00:24:45,000
The winner takes all.

446
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:54,133
What now?

447
00:24:54,267 --> 00:24:55,233
What have you got?

448
00:24:55,567 --> 00:24:57,333
I always win.

449
00:24:57,467 --> 00:24:58,567
Always.

450
00:24:58,700 --> 00:25:01,800
This match won't end
without me being the winner!
